{
  "texts": [
    "As shown in Fig. 1 (a) & (b), SSH achieves comparable performance in both instruction tuning with the LLaMA3.1-8B model and image classification with the ViT 85.8M model, with significantly fewer parameters than LoRA and FourierFT.",
    "Fig. 1(c) & (d) further demonstrate its superior computational efficiency, requiring 55% fewer GFLOPs than FourierFT.",
    "This is due not only to reduce the parameter count but also to avoid the complex num-ber handling required by FourierFT, where real and imaginary parts must be processed separately.",
    "Concretely, our contribution is threefold.",
    "• We introduce SSH, a novel PEFT method based on discrete Hartley transform."
  ]
}